title: WHITE CHICKEN CHILI
directions: Over medium heat, pour oil into a large heavy bottomed pot or Dutch oven. Add onions and cook until softened (about 10 minutes).
Add spices, chicken stock and milk. Bring to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes.

Add chilies, beans, vinegar, chicken and Crema Mexicana Agria. Taste, and add salt and cayenne pepper as needed. Garnish each serving with crumbled cheese, green onions and fresh cilantro sprigs. Serve immediately.
